The paper deals with the generation of periodic discrete structures, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Discrete Fourier Transform theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) category. The generation of structures involves the application of kernels and homogenization theory, which are related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
